INSERT INTO `vaccancies` VALUES (31,'Tooling Technician','','Penang','02 Nov, 2018','<ul>\r\n	<li>Tools testing.</li>\r\n	<li>New tools fabrication.</li>\r\n	<li>Problem solving on tools.</li>\r\n	<li>Compilation of tool test report.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma in Engineering (Mechanical) or equivalent.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in Plastic Injection Moulding Industries will be an added advantage.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates who have knowledge in operating miling, surface grinding EDM machine / moulding and tooling functions / tooling structure design are encouraged to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Full-Time position(s) available.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:careers@cpipenang.com\" href=\"mailto:careers@cpipenang.com\">careers@cpipenang.com</a> before <strong>31st December, 2018</strong>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.<br></p>',0,'2019-12-13 08:48:15','2019-12-13 08:48:15'),(32,'QA Engineer','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<ul>\r\n	<li>Handle customer quality complaints and claims.</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for investigating failures, root causes through 8D approach.</li>\r\n	<li>Liaison between internal departments and customers on quality related matter.</li>\r\n	<li>Drive internal team on continuous improvement projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform data analysis, reports and presentation.</li>\r\n	<li>Improvement of process implementation of quality system activities in relation to ISO policies and procedures.</li>\r\n	<li>Supporting QMS and EHS certification.</li>\r\n	<li>Performing internal, external and 3<sup>rd</sup> party audits.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul><li>Bachelor\'s degree or equivalent in Mechanical, Electrical, or Manufacturing Engineering</li><li>2+ years\' of industry experience</li><li>Strong knowledge of quality tools used in the industry</li><li>Analytical and quantitative approach to problem solving</li></ul>','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\" href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>',1,'2019-12-30 03:42:47','2019-12-30 03:42:47'),(33,'Mould Designer','','Penang','02 Nov, 2018','<ul>\r\n	<li>Responsible for control and manage tooling design requirements for new projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare documentation, system design, equipment and drawing submissions.</li>\r\n	<li>To carry out product fabrication and qualification and DFM analysis report.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>Possess at least 2-3 years experiences in design and manufacture tooling to cut out, emboss for plastic injection moulding.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to read international standard blue print, tolerances is critical.</li>\r\n	<li>Technical college with strong background in 2D & 3D CAD design and CAM.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand and able to operate system such as Pro E, Unigraphic, Solid work, AutoCAD.</li>\r\n	<li>Proactive and must be able to work independently.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:careers@cpipenang.com\" href=\"mailto:careers@cpipenang.com\">careers@cpipenang.com</a> before <strong>31st December, 2018</strong>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.<br></p>',0,'2019-12-13 08:48:02','2019-12-13 08:48:02'),(34,'Supervisor or Line Leader','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<ul>\r\n	<li>Lead a group of operators to run the production.</li>\r\n	<li>Feedback to supervisor on quality and output.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul><li>SPM and possess at least 2 years experiences in manufacturing environment.</li><li>Able to work with minimal supervision.</li></ul>','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>.&nbsp;Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>\r\n',1,'2019-12-30 03:43:18','2019-12-30 03:43:18'),(35,'Assistant Process Engineer','','Penang','02 Nov, 2018','<ul>\r\n	<li>Responsible for production build preparation and coordination of laser & spraying processes.</li>\r\n	<li>To update specifications and generate work procedures (SOP/WI).</li>\r\n	<li>To identify and report on process improvement opportunities.</li>\r\n	<li>To involve and participate in process validation and process improvement initiatives.</li>\r\n	<li>To analyze and resolve work problems, by reviewing yield data, Process Control Chart.</li>\r\n	<li>To prepare, review and update work instructions (WI), FMEA.</li>\r\n	<li>To investigate quality problems and explore preventive actions.</li>\r\n	<li>To provide training to operators and technicians.</li>\r\n	<li>To apply 5S and maintain safe working environments on production.</li>\r\n	<li>To support production daily output, strive to achieve customer requirements on the quality issue and shipment delivery.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidate must possess at least a Professional Certificate, Diploma, Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma, Bachelor\'s Degree, Post Graduate Diploma, Professional Degree, Engineering (Chemical) or equivalent.</li>\r\n	<li>Required language(s): Bahasa Malaysia, Chinese, English.</li>\r\n	<li>At least 1 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</li>\r\n	<li>Preferably Junior Executives specializing in Manufacturing/Production Operations or equivalent.</li>\r\n	<li>Well versed in computer knowledge.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to multi-task and work independently.</li>\r\n	<li>Full-Time position(s) available.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a href=\"mailto:careers@cpipenang.com\">careers@cpipenang.com</a> before <strong>31st December, 2018</strong>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>\r\n',0,'2019-12-13 08:47:50','2019-12-13 08:47:50'),(36,'Project Engineer','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<p><em><u>BROAD RESPONSIBILITIES:</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coordination of all technical activities on assigned projects. Plan, schedules, conducts and coordinates assigned engineering work; monitors work for compliance to applicable standards; accepted engineering practices; ensure effective communication and coordination on assigned projects between all disciplines and all other project participants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:9.0pt;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:9.0pt;\"><em><u>SPECIFIC RESPONSIBILITIES & AUTHORITY:</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Responsible for planning, scheduling, conducting and coordinating the technical and management aspect of projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Accountable for the successful completion of engineering projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Requires extensive regular contacts with assigned project customer.</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in the preparation of engineering project proposals.</li>\r\n	<li>Participating in customer/contractors meetings and resolve customer/engineering and management project issues.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure effective engineering and customer communications.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u>OTHER RESPONSIBILITIES:</u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>BOM preparation thru detail project matrix creation.</li>\r\n	<li>APQP and PPAP compiling</li>\r\n	<li>Coordination and checking of engineering deliverables.</li>\r\n	<li>Monthly project status monitoring report thru project KPI</li>\r\n	<li>Processing and coordination of customer/internal ECN.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform any other related duties assigned by Section Head or Assistant Manager.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelor of Science degree in any engineering field or Diploma holder with over 2 years working experience in any engineering capacity.</li>\r\n	<li>Must posses the ability to read and interpret prints/specs, technical writing, and organizational/management skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to handle multiple priorities, stress, detailed work, reasoning, deadlines. Must be flexible, analytical, and posses excellent communication and interpersonal skills. Will be interacting with multiple departments and working independently.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\" href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>',1,'2019-12-30 03:44:03','2019-12-30 03:44:03'),(37,'Shipping Officer','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<ul>\r\n	<li>To ensure smooth running of the local trucking and overseas import and export sections.</li>\r\n	<li>Advise customers/suppliers on the routing and mode of transportation for shipments.</li>\r\n	<li>Expedite timely preparation of finished goods by store for dispatch before due date.</li>\r\n	<li>Issuance of Certificate of Origin as per customer request.</li>\r\n	<li>File insurance claim for missing / damage outgoing shipments.</li>\r\n	<li>Co-ordinate L/C shipments requirement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma, Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma, Logistic/Transportation or equivalent.</li>\r\n	<li>At least 2 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</li>\r\n	<li>Good knowledge on local trucking, oversea export and import procedures, liaison with relevant Government authorities</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to interpret customs procedures and tariff codes. </li>\r\n	<li>Preferably Junior Executives specializing in Logistics/Supply Chain or equivalent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\" href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>',1,'2019-12-30 03:43:49','2019-12-30 03:43:49'),(38,'Storehand','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<ul>\r\n	<li>Prepare daily shipment.</li>\r\n	<li>Arrange the goods to location.</li>\r\n	<li>Housekeeping.</li>\r\n	<li>Carry out the stock count.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul><li>SPM and possess at least 2 years experiences in manufacturing environment.</li><li>Able to work with minimal supervision.</li></ul>','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\" href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>',1,'2019-12-30 03:43:31','2019-12-30 03:43:31'),(39,'FA Technician','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<ul>\r\n	<li>The incumbent is fully responsible and accountable for the efficient execution of all assigned tasks in the <strong>Quality Assurance</strong> <strong>Department</strong> and other work areas as delegated by the<strong> QA Engineer / QA Assistant Engineer</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>He/She is also authorized to handle all <strong>Quality</strong>, administrative issues, generate all requested <strong>Quality</strong> reports and other relevant documents, coordination of all given instructions and use any equipment assigned to him/her in the most cautious manner.</li>\r\n	<li>May be assigned tasks in other work areas by the QA Engineer / QA Assistant Engineer as and when required.</li>\r\n	<li>To perform any additional assignments as instructed by the QA Engineer / QA Assistant Engineer and to maintain the professional competence, knowledge and skills in the performance of all assigned responsibilities.</li>\r\n	<li>Report to the QA Engineer/ QA Assistant Engineer in a timely manner of any important aspects and problems related to assigned responsibilities.</li>\r\n	<li>Carry out inspection based on customer\'s drawing</li>\r\n	<li>In-process product measurement</li>\r\n	<li>Reliability tests (e.g. temperature, humidity chamber, abrasion, and chemical tests)</li>\r\n	<li>To ensure that all inspectors adhere to the inspection standards and proper methods</li>\r\n	<li>Liaise with production and engineering department</li>\r\n	<li>Follow up with production on corrective & preventative actions</li>\r\n	<li>To carry out other tasks assigned by superior when required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>minimum 1year experience in the related field</li>\r\n	<li>must able to understand and ready all 2D drawing requirement</li>\r\n	<li>carry out routine task for First article full dimension measurement as per 2D drawing requirement and able to program measuring method using CMM</li>\r\n	<li>must understand and read Geometric Dimensioning and & Tolerancing symbols in the 2D drawing and requirement</li>\r\n	<li>competent to identify which equipment to be use for the particular dimension mention in the 2D drawing and following strict methodology to achieve result</li>\r\n	<li>must complete task within time frame with accuracy</li>\r\n	<li>completed to operate and use all measuring equipment, particularly CMM and QV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a data-cke-saved-href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\" href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>',1,'2019-12-30 03:43:04','2019-12-30 03:43:04'),(42,'Clerk','','Penang','02 Dec, 2019','<ul>\r\n	<li>Prepare daily activity for indirect material</li>\r\n	<li>To carry out all administration work related to manufacturing operation.</li>\r\n	<li>To direct and co-ordinate the activities of allocated area of the plant or line total production function</li>\r\n	<li>To cooperate with the superior</li>\r\n	<li>Any other job assigned by the superior from time to time</li>\r\n	<li>To observe Safety, Good Housekeeping & Discipline Control</li>\r\n	<li>To practice Cost Saving Exercise</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Accountability</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To ensure all day to day jobs are completed</li>\r\n	<li>To come out with weekly and monthly report on production</li>\r\n	<li>To report to the superior for any abnormalities related to the job</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n','<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimum SPM</li>\r\n	<li>At least 1-2 year of experience and knowledge in PC</li>\r\n	<li>Able to communicate, write in Bahasa & English and Mandarin</li>\r\n	<li>Able to use computer and familiar with MS Office  Words/Excel/Powerpoint</li>\r\n	<li>To adhere and compliance of ISO9001 quality system requirement</li>\r\n	<li>Good at numbers, calculations and use of statistical tools to analyse data</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p>If you possess the requirements as stated above, you are invited to submit a comprehensive resume stating your current and expected remuneration with a recent passport sized photograph (non-returnable) to the following address or e-mail to <a href=\"mailto:xctan@cpi.com.my\">xctan@cpi.com.my</a>. Only short listed candidates will be notified.</p>\r\n',1,'2019-12-30 03:42:34','2019-12-30 03:42:34');
